      <tr><td colspan=1  style='font-size: 9.5px;'>47 threads, <a href=item.html?item=6101&start=0>1</a> <a href=item.html?item=6101&start=25>2</a>  page(s) long</td><td  style='font-size: 9.5px;' align=right>&nbsp;<a href=item.html?item=6101&start=25>Next Page</a></td></tr></table></form><ul><table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f105413776370781>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=item.html?item=6101&mid=105413776370781>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=item.html?item=6101&mid=105413776370781>If you need an opinion...</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=6101&mid=105413776370781#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, May 28th 12:44 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=81896><span id= >Dragan</span></a><br><span id=notbold>1 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Since you asked for a constructive advice about who should receive the item first, I'll put in my 2 cp (and yes, I have raided NToV, and a number of Luclin/PoP bosses).<br><br>Giving all the gear to coupla main tanks and pullers never works in the long run. Why? You may think, with a better tank you will be able to handle bigger mobs, and everything will go easier. But that's not all that will happen.<br><br>First thing that happens is that all the other people, who get skipped although they put in as much effort as the preferred ones, and in some cases even more effort, they will be pissed off. Some of them may leave.<br><br>Then when you gear up a tank or two with all the choice gear, he can simply leave for a higher level guild. I HAVE SEEN IT HAPPEN PERSONALLY.<br><br>Then you got several problems<br><br>- A lot of the gear that your guild acquired is simply lost. Distributing it more fairly would decrease the damage when someone leaves.<br><br>- Other people are even more pissed off because they sacrificed for that tank (or puller) and he left, thus making their sacrifice worth nothing. More of them may leave.<br><br>- Your guild will have poorly equipped tanks (because you didn't give gear to others). You will be practically bounced coupla months back. The guild will need more time just to reequip some tanks to be able to raid what it raided so far, and that will make even more people leave.<br><br>In my opinion, only a straight point system, precisely made so that there is no amassing of points (so that you have approximately the same amount of points coiming in and going out, for the entire guild together, in a period of time), and items are given to the bidder with most points without any rolls or restrictions (except basic class restrictions, that is, one must be able to use the item and it must be an upgrade for him/her), can work in a long run.<br><br>Aethor<br>The Nameless<br><br><br></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan=2 align=right class=mform id=fs8>0 Replies</td></tr>
