	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=item.html?item=6101&mid=102815696617565>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=item.html?item=6101&mid=102815696617565>Regarding haste.</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=6101&mid=102815696617565#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Jul 31st 7:22 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=43695><span id=Sage>Argfeld</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>71 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Regarding the statement that haste over FBSS doesn't matter:<br><br>Alt-XP is important and some melee types get it solo, meaning they have no source of enchanter/shaman haste.&nbsp;&nbsp;In circumstances like that, they want to have the highest haste they can get off an item.  I don't know about other melee classes, but monks routinely solo XP at all levels, including 60.  Even the &quot;uberest&quot; of guilds don't have many people that have all the Alt-XP they could desire.  I don't know if any players have yet acquired the maximum Alt-XP available though I am sure that goal will be achieved one day.<br><br>Regarding the statement about 51% haste:<br><br>Currently, the game only supports a maximum of 40% or 41% item haste.  They tried to make it higher (45% ?) for some of the ToV items, but it didn't work right and they had to set the items back to 41%.  I think they should be able to easily code for a higher haste if they really want to.  <br><br>Regarding who the item goes to:<br><br>It is awarded to someone based on whatever your guild's loot rules are for said item.  This might be merit-based, point-based, etc.  If you don't agree with the way your guild gives such items out, then find a new guild.  Admittedly, this item would be better for hybrids than for pure melee types in my opinion (I'm a monk - pure melee).<br><br>Regarding non-melee getting this item:<br><br>It could happen, if (as someone pointed out) the guild is so &quot;uber&quot; that all the melee have better.  It could also happen under certain point systems although most casters would prefer to save their precious points for something else.  Also, most casters would recognize the value of this item to a melee person and would not want to harm their guild by using their points on it when a melee person needed it.<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
